COOK!<br><br>
Rock and Roll!<br><br>
Yes! There are some tunes that set me off, too!<br><br>
Micro flashbacks- <br><br>
I have them frequently. Some are nothing, a smell, a picture in the mind, a feeling, fear from nowhere, sounds. Some are pretty intense. They are triggered by sharp sounds, situations, seeing children abused (I go nuts), airplanes, airports, restaurants, crowds ( I can't be in the middle), the things that take me back to stuff that I only speak about with BOC and other trusted people. Some of the stuff still really, really hurts, and I have difficulty in dealing with it still. They all make me want to do something active! Run, hide, attack, pace, prowl, move, never get sleepy, wake up wide awake in night sweats, whatever. I like movement. Sitting still has a low tolerance. I take drives in my car beacuse it is a safe place and I can let down my guard and relax. The feelings are real, the images are real, my actions are real. They all belong back in time 27 years ago.<br><br>
I had one odd one last summer. While out buying photography equipment with my younger daughter--WHAM! - I was back in 'Nam walking the dusty main drag of DiAn with a bunch of photos in my hand and the Cobras were on their way out on a path over my right shoulder,- thwump, thwump, thwump. Sound, smell, feeling, touch, light, dark, seeing, thoughts, all there. It was just for a moment. Nothing very scarey, kind of mundane, ordinary, boring, but I was there. I have had this one infrequently.<br><br>
Megaflashbacks-- <br><br>
For me these are dissociated stated where I am acting out a &quot;combat mission&quot; with everything. These states can go on for days, weeks, months. It is as if I were back in 'Nam in a today setting. Work becomes &quot;the mission&quot;. Home life causes other problems with &quot;the mission&quot;. I &quot;loose time&quot;. The results of all this really suck. You know the rest!<br><br>
The 4th of July can blank me right out.<br><br>
There is a lot more I haven't yet fished out of my head. Maybe I never will understand it all. My goal is to learn how to control it so I can feel better about myself, and others can feel better about me. To really have a life.<br><br>
